<div class="container">
    <h1>Welcome to Web Communication</h1>
    <p>This chapter will introduce you to the fundamentals of how web applications communicate over the internet. You will learn about clients, servers, browsers, HTTP protocols, client-side and server-side communication, and APIs.</p>

    <h2>What You Will Learn</h2>
    <ul>
        <li><strong>The Client:</strong> Understanding the role of the client in web communication.</li>
        <li><strong>The Server:</strong> How servers respond to client requests.</li>
        <li><strong>The Browser:</strong> How web browsers display content and interact with servers.</li>
        <li><strong>HTTP Protocol:</strong> How requests and responses work over the web.</li>
        <li><strong>Client-Side & Server-Side:</strong> Differences, responsibilities, and examples.</li>
        <li><strong>APIs:</strong> How applications exchange data using APIs.</li>
    </ul>

    <p>Use the navigation below to start exploring the chapter topics one by one.</p>

